fields.type: OSM tag, more specific than class

fields.bike_lane: Text. Has a value if there is a bike lane that is part of the road itself. This is different from a separated cycle track, which will be shown as its own line. Possible values are 'right', 'left', 'both' (bike lane on right, left, or both sides of the street respectively), 'yes' (bike lane present but location not specified), 'no' (area was surveyed and confirmed to not have a bike lane), and null (presence of bike lane unknown).
fields.iso_3166_1: Text. The ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 code of the country/territory the feature is in.
fields.iso_3166_2: Text. The ISO 3166-2 code of the state/province/region the feature is in.
fields.lane_count: Number. Number of lanes in the road
fields.layer: Number. Specifies z-ordering in the case of overlapping road segments. Common range is -5 to 5. Available from zoom level 13+.
fields.len: Number. Approximate length of the road segment in Mercator meters.
fields.name: Local name of the road
fields.name_script: Primary written script of the local name
fields.name_zh-Hans: Simplified Chinese name of the road
fields.name_zh-Hant: Traditional Chinese name of the road
fields.oneway: Text. Whether traffic on the road is one-way. One of: 'true', 'false'.
fields.ref: Text. Route number/code of the road.
fields.reflen: Number. How many characters long the ref tag is. Useful for shield styling.
fields.shield: Text. The shield style to use. See the vector tile documentation for a list of possible values.
fields.shield_text_color: Text. The color of the text to use on the highway shield.
fields.structure: Text. One of: 'none', 'bridge', 'tunnel', 'ford'. Available from zoom level 13+.
fields.surface: Whether the road is paved or not (if known). One of: 'paved', 'unpaved'
fields.type: In most cases, values will be that of the primary key from OpenStreetMap tags.

fields.worldview: One of 'all', 'CN', 'IN', 'US'. Use for filtering boundaries to match different worldviews.
